<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1340,1691]" pageId="16" pageNumber="533">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1557,1583]" pageId="16" pageNumber="533">Remarks:</emphasis>
This species was described in 2015 by 
<collectingRegion box="[756,859,1557,1583]" country="Turkey" name="Karaman" pageId="16" pageNumber="533">Karaman</collectingRegion>
G.S. and is the only known 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schiodte" authorityYear="1849" box="[1173,1290,1557,1583]" class="Malacostraca" family="Niphargidae" genus="Niphargus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="533" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1173,1290,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="533">Niphargus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Thasos Island, in the northern 
<collectingRegion box="[404,490,1593,1619]" country="Greece" name="Voreio Aigaio" pageId="16" pageNumber="533">Aegean</collectingRegion>
Sea. Its ecology is yet unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="533" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1340,1691]" pageId="16" pageNumber="533">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,1629,1655]" pageId="16" pageNumber="533">Etymology:</emphasis>
This species is dedicated to deceased scientist Prof. Dr. Spasenija Karaman from 
<collectingRegion box="[1237,1340,1629,1655]" country="Serbia" name="Novi Sad" pageId="16" pageNumber="533">Novi Sad</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry box="[1354,1429,1629,1656]" name="Serbia" pageId="16" pageNumber="533">Serbia</collectingCountry>
) for her excellent studies of Oligochaeta from the Balkan Peninsula.
</paragraph>
